en_136325_0	Rehabilitation Commissioner General Major General JanakaRatnayake has said that more than 12,000 former LTTE cadres have been rehabilitated.
en_136325_1	He further said that many programmes had been launched to uplift their livelihood.
en_136325_2	Major General JanakaRatnayake said the war ended in 2009 May.
en_136325_3	However rehabilitation work was carried out before the war ended.
en_136325_4	He said that the some 12,000 had already been rehabilitated.
en_136325_5	The Rehabilitations Commissioner General was speaking at a function held at the Punthottam Rehabilitation Camp.
en_136325_6	Milch cows were handed over to fifteen families that had been successfully integrated into society after being rehabilitated in the North.
en_136325_7	It was revealed that many such families had been assisted in engaging in dairy farming after being given vocational training.
